      <h3>Why a stand beats a stack of books</h3>
      <p>Books wobble, block vents, and look terrible on video calls. A proper stand keeps your screen at eye level, which straightens your spine and reduces neck strain within the first week. The aluminum frame also acts as a heatsink, dropping CPU temps by 5-10°C compared to flat-on-desk use.</p>

